{
  "$schema": "larder/diet-matrix@1",
  "description": "Harvest plan for the 10,000+ recipe, every-diet catalogue. The Engine (ingestion/sources/edamam.js + the checkpointed backfill in ingest.js matrix mode) walks `diets[]`, and for each diet sweeps the cartesian product of cuisines x mealTypes, issuing one Edamam Recipe Search query per cell with the diet's edamamHealth[]/edamamDiet[] params plus cuisineType + mealType. Each cell paginates via _links.next until `estPerQuery` is reached, the tier page-cap is hit, or the diet floor is met. Every returned recipe is deduped by `dedup` (recipe URI) across the WHOLE matrix, so the 10,000 are UNIQUE even though recipes are multi-labelled and reappear under several diets. Edamam recipes are LINK-OUT only: instructions=null, instructionsExternal=true, publisher set, 'Powered by Edamam'. The top1000 pass (topPriorityDishes) runs FIRST via the keyword `q=` endpoint so the 'Most popular' sort and home rails are dense from day one; those dishes are also QA'd before the bulk sweep. Per-diet floors are MINIMUMS the audit phase loops harvest/curation against, never a budget.",
